Fields.DialogueText: Kanchou, we're picking up a party of Morganas to our south.
They seem to be tracking toward the Senkaku Islands, improbable as it seems.
Your orders?

Fields.MenuText: Well, we're going to go fight them, obviously.
Kumano? Where's the usual guy?
Great, more Morganas... there's no end to the bastards.

Fields.DialogueText: Yes, Kanchou. I thought you'd say that. And we'll win.
Oh, he should be right behind me. I'm certain he'll join us as quickly as he's able.
It seems that way sometimes, doesn't it? Well, more for us.
Captain, we've... we've encountered... encounter...
Catch your breath, officer. I already told Kanchou.
What...? Damn it...
What, did you run here?
We raced.
It wasn't a race.
Says the loser.
Kumano...

Fields.MenuText: No more racing with the crew. It's really not fair.
You didn't cheat, did you?
As captain, I crown you fastest on board. Happy?

Fields.DialogueText: Fine, but I want you to know I gave him a fighting chance. He's just not that quick.
Depends on how you define cheating.
Incandescent.
Now let's go destroy some Morganas.
@BATTLE
With pleasure.
Good day, Kanchou. Are you just sitting down for lunch?
Yeah, you just finishing up?
No, I'll probably be here for another few minutes or so.
Doing what? Just sitting with your trash?
Could you move a little to your left?
Sure...
Oh, yes, that's one.

Fields.MenuText: Did you just throw trash at me?
Nice throw. I never had a very good arm, personally.
I hope you would've picked it up if you'd missed.

Fields.DialogueText: No, I threw trash past you. It's an important distinction.
I've improved. So can you.
Of course. I'm not an animal.
So, what exactly are you doing?
I'm trying to beat my record. My top score is fifteen items successfully thrown away in a row.
Pretty impressive. I take it you do this a lot, then.
It's a daily ritual. It's not my favorite game, but it's something to do between Morganas.
*ALARM*
I'm blaming you for that.
I wish I could summon them on command. Imagine the training I could get done...
@BATTLE
Hey, watch where you're shooting! You almost hit me there!
I'm- I'm sorry. It was an accident. I obviously didn't mean to.
Oh, yeah, obviously! You got a problem with me, buddy?
No, I...
Because I got a problem with you, all right!
Men, please settle. Can't we save the fighting for the Morganas?
Stay out of this, Belle! I'm gonna make sure this guy hits his target ne...  Wha!
Insubordination.
*THUD*
Ughh...
My name is Kumano. And you need to sit down before someone gets hurt.
Thank you.

Fields.MenuText: Is he going to be all right?
That was great, Kumano. I didn't realize you were so strong.
I was just about to step in too.

Fields.DialogueText: He'll be fine. The only thing keeping him down now is shame.
It's not really strength. I used his own momentum against him. He knocked himself over.
Well, you'll have to be quicker if you want to beat me to the punch.
What was that?
Better question. I practice Aikibudo. Are you familiar?
No, but maybe you could teach me sometime.
Hmmm... that might be an interesting challenge. I'll think about it.
@BATTLE
I have effective authority in cases of petty misconduct. I invoked it.
No, I mean that technique you used.
Kumano?
Ah. Taking in the sights?
That is absolutely gorgeous.

Fields.MenuText: Thank you. I work out.
What? I can't see anything past that mountain in the way.
You're right... I really don't take a lot of time to appreciate the view out here.

Fields.DialogueText: I'm not talking about you. Can't you see the mountain? It's practically glowing against the sky.
I'm referring to the mountain, Kanchou. The skyline is gorgeous this time of day.
You should. It's an almost perfect way to experience the beauty of the world.
So this is what you're always doing when you're out on deck?
Yes, mostly.
And here I was thinking you were standing watch for Morganas.
I can do two things at once, Kanchou. I pride myself on it.
*ALARM*
I think you missed one.
I think our lookouts need to work on their response time.
@BATTLE
Oh, yes, nice mountain, real pretty.
Too late. Moment over.
It's just a mountain. I don't really see the big deal.
If you can't appreciate it, you can leave, Kanchou.
Almost perfect? What would be better?
If we were closer to the mountain.
Kumano... what... what is that?
Hmmm? Oh, you mean my game?
Is that what that is?
Yes. It's kind of like shogi, but with modified rules.
Shogi? I'm looking at chess pieces and checkers.
As I said. Modified.

Fields.MenuText: Did Shogi get too easy for you or something?
I guess that explains why you're playing alone.
Your idea of modified looks a lot like Frankenstein's monster.

Fields.DialogueText: I was just too good at it. I needed a challenge.
No one else wanted to play. They said it looked too complicated. It really isn't.
It's really not that bad. It's easy to follow once you get the hang of it.
Do you want to learn how to play?
Um...
Is that a no?
... This would be a really good time for a Morgana to attack.
I tried to get Officer Pitt to play me, but he just glared. If you don't want to play, just say so.
I don't want to...
*ALARM*
I don't want to have to fight these Morganas, but unfortunately, I do.
Mhmmmm, sure. You'd lose anyway.
Let's focus on the Morganas now, shall we?
@BATTLE
All right, come on, let's do this! I'm not going easy on you just because you're a girl.
That's good. I'm not going easy on you just because you're a weakling.
What's going on over here? What are they doing?
They're going to arm wrestle. He's trying to get a little dignity back.

Fields.MenuText: I hope Kumano doesn't beat him too badly.
Are we betting on this?
They do realize we're fighting a war right now, right?

Fields.DialogueText: You're that sure she'll win?
No, but that's actually a good idea. I'll keep it in mind.
We all have to let off steam somehow.
Sit down already. You're making me dizzy with all your pacing.
Okay, let's do this. On the count of three.
One.
Two.
Three.
*THUD*
What the hell?!
I'll do you a favor and pretend like that took a lot out of me.
*ALARM*
All right, time to break it up, everybody. The real show is about to start.
Kanchou's right. This was barely an appetizer!
@BATTLE
If she loses I'll eat my left shoe.
Nine.
*CLANG*
Ten.
*CLANG*
Eleven.

Fields.MenuText: You're within reach of your trash record, Kumano.
Why don't you play solitaire like a normal person?
Miss. Miss. Miss. Miss. Miss.

Fields.DialogueText: Don't remind me. You'll jinx it.
Solitaire has a lonely connotation to it. I'm having too much fun to be lonely.
Shut up. Shut up. Shut up.
*WHIFF*
Shimatta! That's your fault, Kanchou.
It might've been. Sorry.
It's fine. I'll just do better next time.
I'm sure you will.
Do you want to try?
I'm not going to throw your trash across the room.
I meant with your trash.
*ALARM*
I have better things to do with my time. Let's go kick some ass.
I'll meet you there. I have to clean up that one throw you jinxed.
@BATTLE
... Kumano?! What the hell are you doing?
Huh? Oh, Kanchou, what's wrong?
What are you doing with your head through the hull? Besides freaking me out.
Oh, sorry, I was just... sightseeing. I never noticed how beautiful it is under the ocean.
Could you do that without looking like you'd just been beheaded?
Oh, I didn't even think about that. Did it look really strange?

Fields.MenuText: It looked odd enough to make my heart skip a beat.
I've seen stranger, but be more careful next time.
Actually, knowing you, it could've been a lot stranger.

Fields.DialogueText: Or maybe you were just falling in love.
I'll make it obvious I'm not a headless corpse next time.
Stranger? What do you mean?
*ALARM*
Looks like you'll have to sightsee later.
I guess. Lucky for me, the sights are constantly changing.
That's a good thing?
I get bored easily.
@BATTLE
Wh-what?
Nothing. Just having a little fun.
I'd appreciate it.
Considering your love of games and messing with the crew, the possibilities are endless.
That may be my favorite compliment you've given me.
Hey, Kumano, did you need us to pick up anything while we're in port?
... Hmmmm.
Kumano? You hear me?
KUMANO!
Huh? Oh, what's going on? Did I miss something?
What are you doing over here?
I was just working on something.
Were you... drawing something?
What? Oh, you mean my paper? I just doodle sometimes when I think. I make diagrams and stuff.

Fields.MenuText: What were you thinking about?
Doodle? Like what?
Do you have to make that sound to think?

Fields.DialogueText: Nothing important.
Whatever comes to mind, I suppose.
I guess I don't even notice I'm doing it.
*ALARM*
Hold that thought. It sounds like Morganas are closing in on the port.
Then I hope we've restocked enough to handle a little combat.
@BATTLE
... Maybe some paint.
Pardon?
Nani mo nai. Just thinking out loud...
Kanchou, you ready?
Ready? For what?
You said you wanted me to teach you some Aikibudo. I hope you're ready to learn how to fight.

Fields.MenuText: I meant more like teach me some of the history and stuff.
I've been looking forward to this. Let's go.
You know, thinking it over, I might be better off letting you handle the close quarters stuff.

Fields.DialogueText: I'll go over that too. But you don't get one without the other.
Eager. I like that in a student.
You're not getting out of this that easily. In fact, I'm not letting you out of this at all.
*ALARM*
Saved by the alarm.
Maybe if we get close enough to the Morganas, you can show me some moves in action.
Hmmm, that could be fun. You'd have to get us close enough first.
We'll see.
@BATTLE
All right, we're going to play a game.
What? What are you doing?
I'm bored. Teach me how to play your chess-shogi-checkers monster.
You think you can handle it? Many greater men have been humiliated in that chair.

Fields.MenuText: Really? I thought we just picked this one up at port the other day.
I can handle it. I'm stronger than I look.
You're really that worried? Maybe I should rethink this.

Fields.DialogueText: It's a figure of speech. I'm referring to the metaphorical chair.
I hope so. I bore easily.
Too late. You already sat down.
So what's the first thing I need to know about this game of yours?
Probably the name.
That seems important enough. What is it?
Wish I knew. I never gave it one. I'm not good with names.
It might just not need one. Some things are unnamed.
*ALARM*
Morganas, however, are not.
Yes, we can play later. This is a more important game.
You could say that. With far worse odds.
@BATTLE
Heh, I figured you'd say that.
Or far better.
I hope you're ready for another challenge, Kanchou.
What is it this time? Some new-
Oh. Morganas.
If it's not too inconvenient.
Heh. Of course not. There for a minute I thought-
@BATTLE
You know, watching Morganas slip beneath the waves after we've thoroughly demolished them kind of adds something to the seascape.
What do you mean?
I mean the skyline is beautiful, and the ocean's lovely and mysterious, but floating pieces of Morgana refuse after a recent victory is its own kind of gorgeous.

Fields.MenuText: Hmmm, I can see that.
I'm sure I'll see the beauty more when all the Morganas are defeated.
Huh. I guess I'm more of a cat picture person.

Fields.DialogueText: It's kind of like cloud watching, right?
That could take a while. You should try and enjoy the little things you come across on the way.
A what?
If you need me, I'll be in my room. Try not to need me.
I'll do my best. What's the project?
I can see that. See, that one looks like the wreckage of a Morgana. Oh, wait a minute... maybe I'm not good at this game.
Keep working on it. You'll get there.
Don't worry about it.
Well, we could certainly use more of those around the ship.
I get it. At least we won.
And we'll keep winning.
Jumping at shadows, Kanchou? I'm not that intimidating.
A little more sketching. I find myself suddenly inspired.
What's bringing the crowd this time?
They're going at it again. Kumano is defending her title.
You're sure you want to do this again? I mean, haven't you learned anything yet?
The only thing I've learned is that I've got to destroy you if I ever want to be taken seriously.
Well, you might have a point. I definitely don't take you seriously right now, but is darts really how you want to do this?
I've been practicing every chance I've gotten. You might be stronger than me, but I can even the ground with accuracy.
If you say so. I'll let you have the first go at it. Make it a good one.
*SWOOSH*
*THOK*
Heh, not too shabby. Beat that.
You see, there's one problem with this plan of yours.
*SWOOSH*
*THOK*
I perfected this game ages ago.
A bullseye?! Lucky shot.
I don't need luck. I have skill.
*SWOOSH*
*THOK*
*SWOOSH*
*THOK*
Grr...
You want to give up now? I'm running out of bullseye space on the board.
Fine. You win. Again.
Sorry about that. I hope you play again.

Fields.MenuText: That was... impressive.
Did you really have to embarrass him that much?
Can you really just keep throwing bullseyes non-stop?

Fields.DialogueText: Not really. Darts is simple when you learn the trick to it. It becomes boring quickly.
No, but I'm starting to get tired of him. I'm hoping this will keep him from trying again.
Yes. Want to see? ... Oh, I think I broke one of the darts. I hope no one saw.
*ALARM*
Sounds like we'll need to put some of that accuracy of yours to better use.
It's not accuracy, Kanchou. I just know how to throw a dart. I doubt that'll be much help in actual battle.
I don't know. A dart in the eye seems like it'd be pretty painful.
Ugh, don't even say that. It hurts just imagining it.
@BATTLE
And unlike checkers, in my game, your piece can only be kinged by taking one of your own pieces.
Uh... huh...
Kanchou, are you still following?

Fields.MenuText: Uh... huh...?
I... think so. And you can only take a chess piece with a kinged checker, right?
You lost me with the shogi pieces. I'm pretty sure I couldn't even play normal shogi.

Fields.DialogueText: It doesn't sound like it.
Yes, that's right. I'm a little impressed.
Then what made you think you could learn this game?
This is why I play by myself. No one can keep up with me.
Hey, let's just start from the beginning again. I'm sure I can get it this time.
... No, it's fine. I've... I've actually been working on a new game that might be more your speed.
A new game? Is it as complicated as this monster?
No. I'm developing it specifically so less educated individuals can enjoy it too.
Less educated, huh? You know you're actually speaking to one of those "less educated" people, right?
Oh, don't take it personally. I didn't mean anything by it.
*ALARM*
I'll let it pass this time, but only because we have Morganas to fight.
I should give them my thanks then.
@BATTLE
You shouldn't be. I might've said it, but I don't have any idea what it means.
C'mon, it's time to learn something new.
What? I thought we were giving up on learning your game.
Don't tell me I've chosen someone who can't keep up with me.

Fields.MenuText: Hey, I'm your captain, remember?
Ouch. I have feelings.
Depends on if I've had breakfast.

Fields.DialogueText: I don't mean anything by it. You know I have nothing but respect for you.
Don't be so sensitive. They're just words.
Well I hope you've had breakfast, because we're about to burn it off.
You're getting up and I'm going to teach you how to defend yourself.
Oh, Aikibudo...
Exactly. Now get up. I'm not letting you stall for time again.
And what would I be stalling fo...
*ALARM*
Oh, what do you know.
I don't hear anything.
Kumano, come on. They're going to be here any minute.
I hear nothing.
Okay, after the battle, I swear you can put me through whatever paces you have planned. How's that sound?
That... sounds like an alarm. We'd better go fight some Morganas.
@BATTLE
Captain.
Pitt? What are you doing here? Is there a problem on the bridge, or...?
She kept beating me.
If I ever wanted to beat her, this seemed like the best way.

Fields.MenuText: Surprisingly smart coming from you.
She roped me into it by force.
It doesn't really seem healthy to put so much effort and focus into that goal.

Fields.DialogueText: Don't make me add you to my list too.
Really? Because you seem like an excited S.O.B. to me.
If I wanted advice, I'd ask for it.
You best watch yourself, Officer. I don't appreciate insubordination.
Okay you two, are you ready to learn about Aikibudo?
Yes, ma'am.
Sure.
The first thing you need to know is that Aikibudo isn't just a fighting style. It's more of a way of life. A way to protect life.
Aikibudo emphasizes a path that brings balance into your life. It doesn't cause pain, it protects. When I threw you to the ground, did you break anything?
No...
That's because I didn't want you to break anything. Aikibudo brings harmony; it maneuvers around violence. Do the two of you understand?
Yes.
Now, we're going to start with some simple exerci...
*ALARM*
You have to be kidding me.
Seems like we'll have to pick this up later. We're allowed to hurt Morganas, though. Right?
We hurt them so they don't hurt other people. So, yes.
@BATTLE
Kumano, I don't generally protest when Belles pass through walls, but it gets a little bit unnerving when you stop halfway.
This is amazing, Kanchou. I wish you could see it.

Fields.MenuText: Sightseeing again?
Is it odd that I'm now used to seeing headless girls?
I'm fine without seeing whatever odd fish you can see.

Fields.DialogueText: Yes, and it's really something.
It's certainly an odd thing to say out loud. In fact, I'd keep something like that to yourself.
It's not a fish, but it's definitely strange. But in a really cool way.
I can just barely see this glowing, bluish-green plant under us. It's so pretty. I wish I could actually draw so I could show you.
I've seen you draw before. I'm sure you could put something together.
Those are just doodles. I'm not a real artist or anything.
That doesn't sound like you, Kumano. You're not one to be so dismissive about yourself.
... Hmmm. I guess you have a point. I could try it.
*ALARM*
And you should, but after the fight.
Obviously, Kanchou.
@BATTLE
If anyone has that right, it's me. I am the best judge of my own capabilities and how they might...
Haah... haah...
All right, you're both looking good.
Kanchou, I'm actually quite impressed with how fast you can move.

Fields.MenuText: I'm faster than I look, I guess.
You calling me fat?
I'm just trying to impress you, Teach.

Fields.DialogueText: Well, keep it up. You're going to need to be even faster if you want to master Aikibudo.
No. Not anymore. You've been training a lot, after all.
If you're going to give me a title, Kanchou, you can use Sensei.
This is stupid. I feel like I can't go all out like this.
You mean because you're not punching and kicking? How well did that turn out for you before?
Why is it so important to disarm without serious damage?
Well, one: because I'm your commanding officer.
Let me put it this way for you, officer. If you killed your opponent, they wouldn't be able to feel the shame of defeat after you wiped the floor with them.
I'm sure you remember that feeling quite well.
Grr...
*ALARM*
Sounds like this lesson is over.
Perfect timing. I really need to hurt something right now.
@BATTLE
Dammit, I give up. You win. This time.
I knew that three turns ago.
Grr... This isn't over.
What was that about?
Oh, nothing. He thinks he's my rival or something. Like he's anywhere near my level.
He thought he could beat you at chess? That was a mistake.
He's just lucky he didn't choose shogi. I would've crushed him.
Didn't he become your pupil or something?
He quit. The fool doesn't have a lot of patience.

Fields.MenuText: You like toying with him, don't you?
Have time for another game?
He could beat you eventually. Everyone gets lucky.

Fields.DialogueText: Maybe... I haven't really thought about it before. The way one likes worrying at a hangnail, I suppose.
No, I think I'm done with chess for now. If I play it for too long it stops being fun. And he took forever in that last game.
Nobody's that lucky.
*ALARM*
Perfect timing. I needed something to shake up the routine.
Morganas aren't games, Kumano.
Everything's a game if you do it right. But games are only fun if they challenge you.
@BATTLE
So, what do you think?
What... what are these?
They're my drawings. I tried to capture that glowing plant I saw underwater.
Uh...

Fields.MenuText: You did a great job. You really captured the leaves.
It looks like an octopus painted a self-portrait with one of its... non-dominant legs.
You were right. You can't draw.

Fields.DialogueText: There weren't any leaves...
Oh... well, that's kind of what it looked like... maybe.
At least I tried.
Okay, maybe I still need a little practice.
Maybe just a little.
This is a good skill to have, though. It'll help me in the future.
Help you how?
*ALARM*
I have plans, Kanchou. But right now, we have some Morganas that are a little more important.
@BATTLE
I know your sparring partner quit and everything, but I hope you were still able to pick up the basics with me.
Yeah, uh... it was great and all but... nngh... maybe we should call this our last round of training.
Oh, no, why? Don't tell me you're quitting too.

Fields.MenuText: You were just a little rough with me today.
No, I just... aaargh... think I've learned all I can.
I can't feel my... everything.

Fields.DialogueText: I didn't break anything. You're fine.
Trust me, you're barely scratching the surface.
Don't be such a baby. A little strain is good. It means you're growing.
You know, after all that talk about not fighting to hurt your opponent, you sure did a number on me.
Well, I wasn't setting out to. That's the important part. I can't help it if I don't know my own strength.
Captain, we... Oh, you see what I was dealing with now?
Yeah, I see why you quit. What's going on?
Morganas. To the east.
Sound the alarm. Time for a real fight. Can't be any worse than this sparring match.
Stop exaggerating.
@BATTLE
If I have this work like that...
But no, then I couldn't...
Hmmm...

Fields.MenuText: Kumano? Anyone home?
Maybe I should leave her alone.
Thinking again?

Fields.DialogueText: Home... If there was a base, that could get rid of a lot of problems. Then again it could... No, no, that's no good.
Alone... If the units came in one by one then... No, it's easier if they're a group. Right?
It's so close, but I'm just... maybe I'm overthinking it.
Maybe I should just eat lunch in my office.
Oh, Kanchou, how long have you been there?
Not long. What's going on? You're zoning out again.
I'm just trying to finish the basics of my new game.
A new game?
I told you about it, remember? Something simpler. Something that people besides me could play.
Oh, right. You're stuck, huh?
Kind of.
Maybe it'd help if you just didn't think about it for a little bit.
Kanchou, are you kidding? I've never had so much fun in my life!
But you look so-
*ALARM*
Well, I was going to suggest you sleep on it, but it looks like that's not an option.
Never was, Kanchou. I'm going to get to the bottom of this if it's the last thing I do!
@BATTLE
Hey, Kumano, what's in the box?
Hm?
Oh, Kanchou - I have no idea. I'm just helping load the supplies into the storage room.

Fields.MenuText: The crew couldn't handle it themselves?
That's nice of you.
That's... odd for you.

Fields.DialogueText: Apparently it was a little too heavy for them.
I'm a nice person. And I wanted a distraction.
What can I say? I'm helpful. I help all the time. Don't look at me like that.
I was happy to help them out. I needed something to do besides think about my game.
You're really obsessing over that, huh?
I just needed a break. I was starting to run myself in circles.
Captain, Kumano - we have reports of Morganas nearby.
Are they headed our way?
We think so.
Sound the alarm and get the crew on board.
Yes, Captain.
I'd better hurry and stow this.
Yeah. And Kumano, don't give up on this new game. You've put too much effort into it. Don't give up.
Never, Kanchou. I don't know what inspiration will look like when it hits. That's half the fun of the challenge of making it.
@BATTLE
What's the other half?
Improving on my own brilliance.
Humble.
I call these things like I see them. If you were me, you would too.
Kanchou, are you busy right now?
You're not going to toss me around the room again, are you?
No, I wouldn't want to destroy your office. I just wanted to... well, to make sure we're good.

Fields.MenuText: What do you mean?
Of course we're good.
No. You're a horrible person. Obviously.

Fields.DialogueText: I just want to make sure we're, you know... friends.
Good. I thought so, but I just wanted to make sure.
Quit it. I'm being serious here.
I know we joke around sometimes, but I like you, Kanchou. You're one of the good ones.
Well, thanks. I like you too. We're good.
Great. But nevertheless... I've been thinking about Officer Pitt as well.
Maybe that's where he gets his drive to succeed. Spite's a powerful thing.
Born of one's own desire to surpass others. He can find it elsewhere.
I'll be looking forward to it, Kumano. Who knows what you'll create after just a few weeks at this?
*ALARM*
@BATTLE
The hothead, yes. He still hasn't gotten over your thorough trouncing in our training.
That's his own fault. But I'm going to spend less time humiliating him.
This game... and my art... are different. I suppose they've spurred me to surpass myself.
Everyone, in the future. Art is meaningless without an audience.
And we're going to be that audience.
Quite a captive one, too. Muahaha.
Better you take us captive than the Morganas.
Mochiron. They wouldn't know what to do with you.
Okay, what do you think about this? Better, right?
Another drawing? Oh, good job! It looks a lot more like that plant.
I didn't draw the plant this time. I drew myself!
Oh, yeah, I don't see that at all.
Come on, it's obvious. See, the eyes are right here and these are my lips and then my neck and my body. See?
Actually, I do kind of see it now.
What is this for, anyway?
You'll see.
Is this about that game again?
Okay, fine. Yes, it is.
And you're not going to tell me more?
Not yet. When I finish it, though, you'll be the first to play.
I'd better be.
So what do you think, though? The drawing? It's adorable, right?
Oh, yeah. It's about as adorable as you are.
Aww.

Fields.MenuText: Meaning not at all.
But you're still cuter.

Fields.DialogueText: Ouch, Kanchou. You sure know how to charm a girl.
Any softer and you'll absorb my blows when we train.
Too soft?
No, Kanchou. Simply one more strategy to adapt to.
It's a muscle I'm happy to flex.
Oh, I'll flex the rest of them in our training. Relentlessly.
